<p>September, 1917. Monday 17<br/>Day cloudy. Home at 4.30 and slept till 7 breakfast. Slept again till 12 and didn't sleep much in aftn. as big gun firing close by so cleaned up and wrote a little. Out again at 9 and usual job Fritz shelling very heavily all round &amp; we had to take shelter several times and machine gun bullets plentiful. Fixed up our dump for stunt before knocking off and home late &ndash; at 4.</p>
